%20and%20disposable%20income%20situation%2C%26quot%3B%20Laguarta%20said.%20%26quot%3BPart%20of%20that%20is%20also%20pivoting%20between%20in-home%20consumption%20and%20away-from-home%20consumption%20that%20we're%20seeing%20in%20our%20business%20in%20the%20US.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPepsiCo%2C%20which%20owns%20brands%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fall-differences-us-and-uk-mountain-dew-food-wars-2022-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMountain%20Dew%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Lay's%2C%20Cheetos%2C%20and%20Gatorade%2C%20has%20raised%20prices%20in%20recent%20years%20to%20offset%20the%20rising%20costs%20of%20ingredients%20and%20supply-chain%20disruptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20fourth-quarter%20global%20revenues%20were%20down%200.5%25%20year-over-year%20to%20%2427.85%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20North%20America%2C%20sales%20were%20down%20roughly%203.5%25%20to%20%2416.28%20billion.%20This%20came%20from%20sales%20decreases%20of%20about%203%25%20for%20Frito-Lay%2C%202.4%25%20for%20PepsiCo%20Beverages%2C%20and%2015.7%25%20for%20Quaker%20Foods%2C%20which%20is%20by%20far%20the%20smallest%20of%20its%20three%20North%20American%20subsidiaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaguarta%20added%20that%20PepsiCo%20was%20lowering%20its%20guidance%20because%20it%20expected%20the%20trend%20to%20continue%20into%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20PepsiCo%20is%20optimistic%20for%20the%20year%20ahead.%20%26quot%3BWe%20feel%20good%20about%20the%20consumer%20in%20'24%20in%20the%20US%2C%26quot%3B%20Laguarta%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20low%20unemployment%20levels%20and%20an%20expectation%20that%20wages%20would%20rise%20at%20a%20higher%20rate%20than%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20hope%20that%20by%20the%20summer%20interest%20rates%20will%20go%20down%20and%20that%20will%20create%20another%20source%20of%20oxygen%20for%20disposable%20income%20in%20households%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaguarta%20said%20that%20PepsiCo's%20sales%20post-pandemi