ons%20their%20way%20of%20relating%20to%20one%20another%20because%20even%20%5Bthat%5D%20is%20going%20to%20become%20part%20of%20their%20CV.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20Gen%20Z%20is%20an%20%E2%80%9Calienated%E2%80%9D%20group%20because%20of%20how%20social%20media%20has%20shaped%20their%20lives.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20get%20much%20older%2C%20much%20faster%20as%20a%20result%20of%20living%20in%20a%20social%20media%20world%20in%20which%20they%20are%20compelled%20to%20try%20to%20find%20an%20identity%20which%20in%20the%20end%20is%20not%20self-driven.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESocial%20media%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-navigate-social-media-when-your-boss-follow-you-2021-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecreated%20a%20%E2%80%9Cboundary-less%20universe%2C%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20people%E2%80%99s%20professional%20and%20personal%20lives%2C%20Ben%20Voyer%2C%20ESCP%20Business%20School%20professor%20previously%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVoyer%20suggests%20deleting%20phases%20of%20social%20media%20from%20when%20you%E2%80%99re%20young%20and%20wiping%20the%20slate%20clean%20when%20approaching%20graduation%20so%20that%20employers%20don%E2%80%99t%20find%20anything%20unsavory%20when%20they%20Google%20you.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20advises%20workers%20to%20think%20carefully%20before%20posting%20about%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIf%20it's%20very%20important%20to%20who%20you%20are%2C%20to%20your%20identity%2C%20it's%20important%20that%20you%20express%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BBut%20for%20other%20other%20things%2C%20veering%20too%20much%20into%20politics%20is%20probably%20something%20that%20could%20backfire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-cant-separate-work-personal-life-social-media-economist-2024-