r%20action%20against%20Paytm%20Payments%20Bank%20(PPBL)%2C%20RBI%2C%20on%20January%2031%2C%20directed%20it%20to%20stop%20...%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fhardly-any-room-to-review-action-taken-against-paytm-payments-bank-rbi-guv-124021200745_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fhardly-any-room-to-review-action-taken-against-paytm-payments-bank-rbi-guv-124021200745_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fhardly-any-room-to-review-action-taken-against-paytm-payments-bank-rbi-guv-124021200745_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Who%20Decides%20Which%20Prisoners%20Deserve%20an%20Early%20Release%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F12164542%2FDavinderpal_singh_bhullar.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fchandigarh-news%2Fdevinder-pal-singh-bhullar-s-release-request-not-tenable-srb-101706124841103.html%5C%22%3Erecent%20denial%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20premature%20release%20of%20Devender%20Pal%20Singh%20Bhullar%20by%20the%20Delhi%20State%20Review%20Board%20for%20the%20seventh%20time%20calls%20for%20attention%20to%20the%20issue%20of%20convicts%20imprisoned%20for%20extended%20periods%20of%20time%20in%20prisons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhullar%2C%20who%20is%2058%2C%20has%20been%20in%20prison%20for%20close%20to%2026%20years%20now.%20This%20means%20that%20he%20has%20spent%20most%20of%20his%20life%20as%20a%20prisoner.%20Bhullar%20was%20convicted%20in%202001%20by%20the%20TADA%20court%20under%20the%20anti-terrorism%20law%20(TADA)%20for%20an%20explosion%20in%20Delhi%20in%201993%20that%20killed%20nine%20bystanders.%20His%20conviction%20raised%20various%20debates%2C%20given%20that%20the%20entire%20evidence%20against%20him%20was%20based%20on%20his%20%E2%80%98confession%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20his%20family%20and%20lawyers%20maintained%20was%20obtained%20under%20torture%20and%20duress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20all%20other%20accused%20were%20acquitted%20in%20the%20case%2C%20his%20conviction%20was%20predicated%20on%20his%20own%20retracted%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadpan.org%2Findia-case-study-devender-pal-singh%2F%5C%22%3E%C2%A0confession%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20was%20not%20recorded%20in%20written%20or%20electronic%20form%2C%20as%20required%20by%20the%20law%20under%20which%20he%20was%20convicted.%20In%20March%202002%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20affirmed%20his%20death%20sentence%20by%20a%20split%20verdict%20of%202%3A1%2C%20with%20the%20presiding%20judge%20who%20acquitted%20him%20due%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20evidence%20and%20cast%20doubts%20on%20the%20authenticity%20of%20his%20confession.%20It%20was%20later%20in%202014%20that%20a%20five-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20commuted%20his%20death%20sentence%20to%20life%20imprisonment%2C%20reversing%20its%20two-bench%20judgment%20which%20had%20refused%20to%20commute%20his%20death%20sentence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2FPolitics%2Fl5Q63GiljsKeGHySXRLDqO%2FSC-commutes-Devinder-Pal-Singh-Bhullars-death-sentence.html%5C%22%3Ereversed%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20decision%20on%20two%20grounds.%20Firstly%2C%20it%20recognised%20the%20medical%20findings%20in%20his%20case%2C%20which%20revealed%20that%20he%20suffered%20from%20major%20mental%20health%20disorders.%20Secondly%2C%20it%20cited%20an%20unexplained%20delay%20of%20eight%20and%20a%20half%20years%20in%20deciding%20over%20his%20mercy%20petition.%20The%20earlier%20two-judge%20bench%20had%20stated%20that%20mere%20delay%20in%20evaluating%20mercy%20appeals%20of%20terror%20convicts%20could%20not%20be%20used%20as%20a%20justification%20for%20commuting%20their%20death%20sentence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20case%20for%20his%20early%20release%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%20433%20of%20the%20Criminal%20Procedure%20Code%20allows%20prisoners%20who%20have%20served%20a%2014-year%20sentence%20in%20prison%20to%20be%20considered%20for%20early%20release.%20The%20primary%20objective%20of%20this%20is%20to%20reform%20inmates%20and%20reintegrate%20them%20into%20society.%20The%20most%20significant%20factor%20for%20their%20release%20is%20whether%20they%20have%20transformed%20into%20harmless%20and%20beneficial%20members%20of%20society%20and%20if%20their%20imprisonment%20will%20serve%20any%20good.%20Judgments%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20have%20ruled%20out%20the%20concept%20of%20%E2%80%9Csavage%20justice%E2%80%9D%20in%20favour%20of%20sentence%20softening%20processes.%20That%20punishment%20ought%20not%20to%20be%20used%20to%20exact%20revenge%20but%20rather%20to%20reform%20and%20rehabilitate%20the%20prisoners%20is%20something%20that%20has%20already%20been%20held%20by%20the%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20provision%20to%20release%2C%20however%2C%20is%20a%20discretionary%20power%20granted%20to%20state-appointed%20sentence%20review%20boards%20that%20propose%20prisoners%20for%20their%20early%20release.%20More%20often%20than%20not%2C%20this%20discretionary%20power%20has%20been%20proven%20to%20work%20not%20just%20in%20a%20bureaucratic%20manner%20but%20also%20in%20tandem%20with%20the%20state%20authorities.%20The%20Bilkis%20Bano%20case%20convicts%20en%20masse%20released%20by%20the%20state%20of%20Gujarat%20have%20already%20shown%20us%20how%20this%20discretionary%20power%20of%20the%20prison%20authorities%20operates%20and%20how%20it%20has%20increasingly%20become%20a%20tool%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20state%20agencies%20that%20issue%20selective%20directives%20depending%20on%20their%20own%20preferences%20and%20agendas.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20Bano%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20while%20setting%20aside%20the%20release%20of%20convicts%2C%20raised%20important%20questions%20over%20this%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Flaw-today%2Fstory%2Fbilkis-bano-case-supreme-court-questions-gujarat-goverenment-centre-2422738-2023-08-17%5C%22%3Earbitrary%20and%20selective%3C%2Fa%3E%20way%20in%20which%20the%20board%20exercises%20its%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fchandigarh-news%2Fdevinder-pal-singh-bhullar-s-release-request-not-tenable-srb-101706124841103.html%5C%22%3Erejection%20of%20Bhullar%E2%80%99s%20plea%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20an%20example%20of%20this.%20His%20case%20was%20rejected%20by%20the%20board%20with%20a%20sole%20dissenting%20vote%20from%20a%20Delhi%20government%20minister%2C%20who%20favoured%20his%20release%20based%20on%20his%20mental%20health%20conditions.%20The%20cyclostyled%20order%20equates%20his%20release%20with%20a%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9Cdirect%20threat%20to%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20sovereignty%2C%20integrity%2C%20and%20tranquility%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20a%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9Csignificant%20threat%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20society.%20The%20comment%20on%20the%20board%20reads%3A%3Cem%3E%20%E2%80%9CThough%20old%2C%20the%20terror%20convict%20still%20poses%20a%20threat%20to%20society%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20that%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Ethe%20possibility%20of%20his%20committing%20crime%20again%20cannot%20be%20ruled%20out.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20comments%20on%20the%20board%20show%20bureaucratic%20mechanical%20reasoning%20where%20the%20sole%20basis%20for%20the%20rejection%20of%20a%20schizophrenic%20disorder-suffering%20prisoner%20%E2%80%93%20a%20serious%20mental%20condition%20that%20impairs%20cognition%20and%20produces%20a%20loss%20of%20reality%20%E2%80%93%20was%20his%20initial%20charge%20of%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20case%20of%20early%20release%20%E2%80%93%20even%20though%20the%20discretionary%20power%20of%20the%20prison%20%E2%80%93%20has%20to%20be%20exercised%20in%20an%20objective%20and%20transparent%20manner%20so%20that%20it%20does%20not%20impinge%20on%20the%20constitutional%20guarantees%20under%20Articles%2014%20and%2021%20as%20stated%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2F754-rashidul-jafar-chota-v-state-of-up-6-sep-2022-434517.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ERashidul%20Jafar%20vs%20State%20of%20U.P.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%3Cem%3E(2022).%20%3C%2Fem%3EIn%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F569426%2F%5C%22%3ELaxman%20Naskar%20vs.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2000)%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20laid%20down%20directions%20that%20mention%20factors%20that%20should%20be%20considered%20while%20considering%20a%20case%20for%20premature%20release%20of%20a%20convict.%20These%20factors%20include%20the%20convict%E2%80%99s%20potential%20for%20committing%20a%20crime%2C%20his%20overall%20conduct%20and%20performance%20in%20jail%2C%20the%20total%20period%20of%20incarceration%20undergone%2C%20their%20rehabilitation%20potential%2C%20and%20the%20socioeconomic%20status%20of%20their%20family.%20In%20addition%20to%20this%2C%20the%20circumstances%20of%20the%20offence%20as%20well%20as%20the%20convict%E2%80%99s%20state%20of%20mind%20at%20the%20time%20when%20the%20offence%20was%20committed%20are%20also%20factors%20that%20ought%20to%20be%20kept%20in%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20reading%20of%20his%20rejection%20order%20shows%20that%20the%20above-mentioned%20factors%20were%20overlooked.%20The%20report%20does%20not%20find%20mention%20of%20his%20conduct%20in%20prison%20or%20during%20parole.%20Furthermore%2C%20there%20is%20no%20explanation%20or%20supporting%20evidence%20that%20justifies%20Bhullar%E2%80%99s%20propensity%20to%20commit%20a%20crime%20in%20the%20future%2C%20considering%20his%20schizophrenia%20condition.%20Despite%20the%20local%20police%20in%20Bhullar%E2%80%99s%20hometown%20raising%20no%20objections%20to%20his%20release%2C%20any%20explanation%20by%20the%20Delhi%20police%20who%20opposed%20his%20release%20as%20to%20how%20releasing%20him%20would%20become%20a%20serious%20threat%20to%20society%20is%20also%20absent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20context%20may%20not%20be%20the%20sole%20ground%20in%20deciding%20a%20case%20for%20early%20release%2C%20the%20context%20of%20Bhullar%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20which%20is%20rooted%20in%20the%20experiences%20of%20the%201990s%20in%20Punjab%2C%20cannot%20be%20discounted.%20This%20was%20when%20the%20state%20engaged%20in%20massive%20extrajudicial%20killings%20and%20disappearances%20in%20Punjab%20which%20his%20father%20and%20uncle%20too%20became%20casualties.%20The%20eyewitness%20account%20and%20his%20mother%E2%80%99s%20complaint%20against%20police%20officials%20at%20a%20Bathinda%20court%20in%202013%20for%20her%20husband%E2%80%99s%20kidnapping%20and%20death%20reveal%20how%20his%20father%20was%20subjected%20to%20enforced%20disappearance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBhullar%E2%80%99s%20rejection%20is%20arbitrarily%20based%20on%20a%20single%20rationale%3A%20the%20nature%20of%20his%20offence.%20For%20this%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1222748%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EMaru%20Ram%20vs.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(1981)%20stated%20that%20even%20the%20most%20%E2%80%9Cserious%E2%80%9D%20offences%20necessitate%20a%20reformative%20approach%20if%20a%20person%20has%20served%20a%20sufficient%20amount%20of%20time%20in%20jail.%20In%20Bhullar%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20his%2026%20years%20of%20long%20imprisonment%20was%20not%20considered%20for%20the%20sole%20reason%20that%20he%20was%20convicted%20on%20terror%20charges.%20The%20arbitrariness%20of%20Bhullar%E2%80%99s%20case%20sheds%20light%20on%20the%20jail%20authorities%E2%80%99%20discretionary%20power%20which%20has%20completely%20fallen%20under%20state%20control.%20This%20arbitrariness%20has%20turned%20Bhullar%E2%80%99s%20into%20a%20%3Cem%3Ebare%20life%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Keeping%20Bhullar%20in%20jail%20is%20a%20travesty%20of%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKawalpreet%20Kaur%20is%20an%20advocate%20based%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707738332000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F12164542%2FDavinderpal_singh_bhullar.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwho-decides-which-prisoners-deserve-an-early-release%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20rejection%20of%20Devender%20Pal%20Singh%20Bhullar's%20plea%20for%20early%20release%20show%20the%20arbitrary%20%E2%80%93%20and%20often%20unfair%20%E2%80%93%20way%20these%20decisions%20are%20made.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fwho-decides-which-prisoners-deserve-an-early-release%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Israel%20should%20'stop%20and%20think'%20on%20Rafah%20offensive%2C%20Cameron%20says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707738060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F02%2F768x432%2Fskynews-palestinians-israeli_6452919.jpg%3F20240212105151%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fisrael-should-stop-and-think-on-rafah-offensive-david-cameron-says-13070060%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Israel%20should%20%26quot%3Bstop%20and%20think%26quot%3B%20before%20taking%20any%20further%20action%20in%20Rafah%2C%20Foreign%20Secretary%20Lord%20Cameron%20has%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fisrael-should-stop-and-think-on-rafah-offensive-david-cameron-says-13070060%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fisrael-should-stop-and-think-on-rafah-offensive-david-cameron-says-13070060%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fisrael-should-stop-and-think-on-rafah-offensive-david-cameron-says-13070060%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22