a%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EParticipants%20in%20Arlington%20said%20they%20cut%20back%20on%20overtime%20or%20weekend%20work%20while%20getting%20better%20jobs%20or%20pursuing%20certifications.%20They%20saw%20improvements%20in%20their%20physical%20and%20mental%20health%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20stronger%20sense%20of%20connection%20to%20their%20communities.%20Parents%20also%20became%20more%20involved%20in%20their%20children%E2%80%99s%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20with%20inflation%20still%20hurting%20the%20wallets%20of%20lower-income%20households%2C%20skyrocketing%20housing%20prices%2C%20and%20the%20lifting%20of%20eviction%20moratoriums%2C%20Arlington%E2%80%99s%20guaranteed%20income%20program%20highlighted%20difficulties%20in%20resolving%20housing%20insecurity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAggregate%20household%20debt%20increased%20during%20the%20program%2C%20while%20many%20said%20they%20were%20still%20severely%20rent-burdened%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20program.%20Even%20though%20four%20in%20five%20households%20had%20local%20housing%20grants%2C%20averaging%20about%20%24711%20a%20month%2C%20the%20median%20household%20paid%2054%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20rent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20nearly%20every%20participant%20said%20they%20were%20better%20off%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20program.%20The%20report%20said%20participants%20%E2%80%9Chave%20more%20bandwidth%20to%20think%20beyond%20getting%20by%20today%20to%20set%20goals%20and%20plan%20for%20tomorrow.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EQualifying%20for%20the%20program%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EParticipants%20were%20eligible%20for%20the%20program%20if%20they%20made%20under%2030%25%20of%20the%20area's%20median%20income%2C%20or%20about%20%2445%2C630%20for%20a%20family%20of%20four.%20That%20group%20includes%20about%2024%2C000%20county%20residents%20who%20are%20disproportionately%20families%20of%20color%20in%20essential%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E150%20families%20were%20selected%20from%20the%20county%E2%80%99s%20housing%20grant%20program%2C%20while%20an%20additional%2025%20were%20households%20with%20immigrants%20lacking%20permanent%20legal%20status%20and%20another%2025%20had%20members%20who%20were%20previously%20incarcerated.%20Slightly%20over%20half%20of%20the%20participants%20were%20African%20American%2FBlack%2C%20while%2030%25%20were%20Hispanic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20report%2C%20the%202023%20median%20annual%20income%20for%20a%20family%20of%20four%20in%20Arlington%20County%20was%20%24152%2C100.%20The%20county%20also%20has%20among%20the%20highest%20housing%20costs%20in%20the%20nation%2C%20data%20from%20the%20Economic%20Research%20Institute%20shows.%20For%20the%2010%25%20of%20households%20making%20under%2030%25%20of%20the%20county's%20median%20income%2C%20median%20living%20expenses%20are%20about%20three%20times%20what%20they%20earn.%20The%20county%20is%20home%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aboutamazon.com%2Fnews%2Famazon-offices%2Famazon-headquarters-hq2-arlington-virginia-photos%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%E2%80%99s%20second%20headquarters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20well%20as%20various%20other%20technology%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20program%20worked%20with%20local%20and%20state%20agencies%20to%20ensure%20these%20cash%20payments%20did%20not%20impact%20participants%E2%80%99%20eligibility%20for%20other%20benefits%20and%20subsidies.%20Participants%20also%20could%20request%20coaching%20for%20long-term%20economic%20planning%2C%20which%20came%20in%20handy%20given%20many%20participants%20were%20newly%20able%20to%20open%20bank%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20participant%20enrollment%20survey%20showed%20that%20only%209%25%20could%20pay%20off%20a%20%24400%20emergency%20expense%20at%20the%20program%E2%80%99s%20start%2C%20while%2060%25%20said%20they%20were%20worried%20about%20running%20out%20of%20food.%20About%20three-fourths%20of%20participants%20said%20they%20were%20employed%20at%20the%20program's%20start.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EParticipants%E2%80%99%20lives%20improved%20%E2%80%94%20but%20housing%20remains%20a%20huge%20concern%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%20two%20in%20five%20participants%20said%20they%20used%20the%20extra%20income%20for%20groceries%20%E2%80%94%20the%20percentage%20of%20participants%20worried%20about%20running%20out%20of%20food%20fell%20from%2061%25%20to%2042%25%20%E2%80%94%20while%20almost%20a%20third%20paid%20bills%20and%20debts.%20Transportation%20access%20was%20another%20major%20improvement%2C%20as%20the%20percentage%20of%20participants%20who%20had%20no%20trouble%20paying%20for%20transportation%20grew%20from%2068%25%20to%2086%25.%20Many%20also%20said%20they%20could%20do%20activities%20as%20a%20family%20beyond%20basic%20needs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%2020%25%20said%20they%20used%20the%20extra%20income%20to%20pay%20rent%2C%20slightly%20less%20than%20those%20who%20used%20it%20for%20miscellaneous%20expenses%20like%20car%20repairs%2C%20medical%20bills%2C%20or%20job%20training.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompared%20to%20the%20control%20group%20that%20didn't%20receive%20payments%2C%20participants%20had%20significantly%20better%20employment%20outcomes.%20While%20the%20percentage%20of%20employed%20control%20group%20families%20stayed%20the%20same%20at%2074%25%2C%20the%20participants%E2%80%99%20employment%20rate%20jumped%20from%2075%25%20to%2087%25.%20About%2092%25%20of%20participants%20%E2%80%94%20compared%20to%2075%25%20of%20control%20group%20households%20%E2%80%94%20reported%20paying%20%241%2C300%20or%20more%20in%20rent%20and%20utilities%20each%20month%20in%20addition%20to%20their%20housing%20grant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20control%20group%20families%20saw%20median%20monthly%20incomes%20from%20work%20rise%20from%20%241%2C280%20to%20%241%2C400%20over%20the%2018%20months%2C%20incomes%20for%20participants%20rose%20from%20%241%2C200%20to%20%241%2C640.%20When%20looking%20only%20at%20employed%20participants%2C%20median%20income%20rose%20from%20%241%2C573%20to%20%241%2C900%20per%20month.%20