feel%20equally%20aggrieved.%20%3Cem%3EWhy%20should%20I%20be%20loyal%20to%20my%20company%20when%20my%20company%20isn't%20loyal%20to%20me%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20my%20surprise%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20older%20readers%20took%20issue%20with%20getting%20lumped%20into%20the%20pro-loyalty%20camp.%20%26quot%3BLoyal%20GenX%20%E2%80%93%20Are%20You%20Kidding%3F%26quot%3B%20read%20the%20subject%20line%20of%20one%20email%20from%20a%20Gen%20Xer.%20Someone%20else%20wrote%2C%20more%20gently%2C%20%26quot%3BWhile%20I%20feel%20you're%20spot%20on%20with%20most%20of%20your%20facts%20you've%20got%20gen%20x%20all%20wrong.%26quot%3B%20They%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BMy%20generation%20leads%20in%20workplace%20dissatisfaction%20and%20realized%202%20decades%20ago%20that%20there%20was%20no%20more%20corporate%20loyalty.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20used%20to%20hearing%2020-somethings%20complain%20about%20the%20state%20of%20corporate%20America%20today.%20But%20I%20didn't%20expect%20to%20receive%20such%20an%20outpouring%20of%20dismay%20and%20disillusionment%20from%20seasoned%20workplace%20veterans.%20I'd%20written%20the%20story%20for%20young%20people%2C%20as%20a%20defense%20of%20their%20decision%20to%20rebel%20against%20the%20notion%20that%20we%20owe%20our%20employers%20a%20debt%20of%20gratitude.%20Instead%2C%20I%20seem%20to%20have%20unintentionally%20tapped%20into%20the%20quiet%20frustration%20of%20more%20experienced%20employees.%20After%20all%2C%20it's%20the%20boomers%20and%20Gen%20Xers%20who%20actually%20remember%20a%20time%20when%20their%20companies%20treated%20them%20better.%20For%20them%2C%20the%20broken%20%26quot%3Bpsychological%20contract%26quot%3B%20I%20described%20in%20my%20story%20isn't%20some%20historical%20artifact.%20It's%20their%20lived%20experience.%20%26quot%3BYou%20summarized%20everything%20I%20experienced%20in%20the%20last%2038%20years%20of%20my%20career%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20reader%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReaders%20told%20me%20they%20have%20watched%20employers