0them.%20%26quot%3BIt%20resonated%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3Bbecause%20I%20still%20see%20company%20leadership%20telling%20us%20to%20give%20it%20our%20all%20and%20make%20sacrifices%20above%20and%20beyond%20to%20make%20the%20company%20prosperous%20%E2%80%94%20prosperity%20that%20we%20are%20very%20unlikely%20to%20share%20in.%26quot%3B%20Contrary%20to%20what%20I%20wrote%2C%20he%20has%20watched%20with%20dismay%20as%20his%20younger%20colleagues%20fall%20for%20the%20company's%20line.%20%26quot%3BI%20see%20many%20people%2C%20particularly%20younger%20employees%20buying%20into%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BMillennials%20badly%20need%20to%20become%20as%20cynical%2C%20demanding%2C%20and%20difficult%20as%20the%20press%20makes%20them%20out%20to%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%2C%20to%20put%20it%20mildly%2C%20the%20way%20I%20had%20framed%20it%20in%20my%20story.%20American%20workplaces%2C%20it%20appears%2C%20are%20full%20of%20Gen%20X%20and%20boomer%20Marxes.%20%3Cem%3EMillennials%20of%20the%20world%20unite!%20You%20have%20nothing%20to%20lose%20but%20your%20chains!%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20comment%20reminded%20me%20of%20a%20conversation%20I%20had%20a%20few%20weeks%20ago%20with%20a%20software%20engineer%20I'll%20call%20Gabriel.%20Last%20year%2C%20he%20was%20devastated%20to%20be%20laid%20off%20from%20his%20very%20first%20job%20out%20of%20college.%20Only%20a%20few%20weeks%20earlier%2C%20executives%20had%20assured%20everyone%20in%20an%20all-hands%20meeting%20that%2C%20while%20times%20were%20tough%2C%20the%20company%20wasn't%20at%20the%20point%20where%20it%20needed%20to%20lay%20people%20off.%20Gabriel%20thought%20he%20deserved%20at%20least%20a%20warning%20that%20the%20cuts%20might%20be%20coming.%20He%20thought%20he%20deserved%20to%20know%20why%20they%20chose%20him%2C%20and%20not%20others%20on%20his%20team.%20He%20thought%20he'd%20be%20rewarded%2C%20as%20a%20high%20performer%2C%20with%20job%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20didn't%20strike%20me%20as%20unreasonable%20expectations.%20But%20as%20we%20talked%2C%20Gabriel%20seemed%20almost%20ashamed%20for%20having%20held%20them.%20He%20blamed%20himself%20for%20ever%20expecting%20his%20employer%20to%20treat%20him%20fairly.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20my%20fault%20for%20even%20feeling%20like%20I%20was%20owed%20anything%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20me.%20Now%2C%20in%20his%20new%20job%2C%20the%20only%20thing%20he%20feels%20entitled%20to%20is%20his%20agreed-upon%20salary%20%E2%80%94%20and%20in%20return%2C%20he%20puts%20in%20eight%20hours%20of%20labor%20a%20day%2C%20five%20days%20a%20week%2C%20and%20not%20a%20minute%20more.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20going%20to%20ever%20go%20above%20and%20beyond%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20how%20Gabriel%2C%20and%20many%20other%20workers%2C%20have%20decided%20to%20even%20the%20scales%20in%20the%20modern%20workplace.%20But%20as%20I%20wrote%20in%20my%20original%20story%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20this%20is%20actually%20the%20world%20most%20of%20us%20want%20%E2%80%94%20a%20kind%20of%20hypertransactional%20relationship%20between%20employers%20and%20employees%20where%20no%20one%20owes%20anyone%20anything%2C%20where%20we%20all%20adopt%20what%20one%20of%20my%20readers%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bmercenary%20mindset.%26quot%3B%20Even%20Gabriel%2C%20who%20has%20adopted%20the%20very%20cynicism%20that%20one%20of%20my%20older%20readers%20urged%2C%20says%20he%20misses%20the%20camaraderie%20he%20felt%20with%20his%20old%20team%2C%20back%20when%20he%20gave%20his%20job%20his%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20felt%20like%20we%20were%20all%20winning%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20the%20world%20to%20be%20like%20this.%20But%20now%20I%20know%20how%20this%20game%20works.%20So%20I'm%20going%20to%20play%20it%20to%20win%20it.%26quot%3B%20He's%20come%20to%20the%20same%20conclusion%20as%20older%2C%20more%20experienced%20workers.%20They%20wish%20loyalty%20was%20still%20rewarded%20by%20their%20companies.%20But%20because%20they%20can%20no%20longer%20expect%20that%2C%20they've%20decided%20to%20adapt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20the%20biggest%20lesson%20for%20me%2C%20based%20on%20all%20the%20emails%20I've%20received%2C%20is%20to%20stop%20pontificating%20on%20differences%20between%20the%20generations.%20But%20I%20can't%20help%20myself%2C%20so%20I'll%20hazard%20one%20more%20sweeping%20generalization%3A%20Maybe%20the%20biggest%20difference%20between%20older%20and%20younger%20workers%20today%20isn't%20how%20they%20feel%20about%20loyalty%2C%20as%20I%20originally%20posited.%20Maybe%20it's%20what%20they're%20%3Cem%3Edoing%3C%2Fem%3E%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20emails%20I%20got%20from%20boomer%20and%20Gen%20X%20and%20even%20millennial%20readers%20were%20tinged%20with%20a%20sense%20of%20resignation%20%E2%80%94%20a%20reluctant%20acceptance%20of%20the%20way%20the%20world%20is%20now.%20Gen%20Z%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20isn't%20quite%20resigned%20to%20that%20reality%20yet.%20From%20the%20office%20to%20TikTok%2C%20they're%20vocal%20about%20their%20displeasure%20with%20the%20state%20of%20work%20today.%20They%20believe%20that%20it%20doesn't%20have%20to%20be%20this%20way%2C%20and%20that%20they%20have%20the%20power%20to%20force%20their%20employers%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20might%20call%20that%20naivete.%20Others%20might%20call%20it%20entitlement.%20But%20the%20older%20workers%20I%20heard%20from%20call%20it%20something%20else.%20They%20call%20it%20about%20damn%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Faki-ito%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EAki%20Ito%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20chief%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-loyalty-gen-z-millennials-gen-x-boomers-employee-engagement-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22