e%20Congress%20in%20the%20RS%20seat%20vacated%20by%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20Manas%20Ranjan%20Bhuniya%2C%20who%20became%20a%20minister%20in%20the%20state%20government.%20The%20term%20of%20the%20seat%20ended%20in%20August%202023%20but%20the%20party%20did%20not%20renominate%20her%20at%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFormer%20Assam%20Congress%20president%20Ripun%20Bora%20heads%20the%20TMC%E2%80%99s%20Assam%20unit%2C%20while%20Dev%20is%20another%20prominent%20leader.%20The%20party%20had%20asked%20from%20the%20Congress%20four%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%2014%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20%E2%80%93%20Karimganj%2C%20Kokrajhar%2C%20Lakhimpur%2C%20and%20Dhubri%20%E2%80%93%20for%20an%20alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ENow%20that%20the%20seat-sharing%20talks%20have%20failed%2C%20the%20TMC%20may%20contest%20in%20one%20or%20two%20more%20seats%2C%20like%20Naogaon%2C%20which%20has%20a%20sitting%20Congress%20MP%20but%20the%20TMC%20claims%20to%20have%20good%20organisational%20strength.%20The%20TMC%20has%20never%20won%20any%20assembly%20or%20Lok%20Sabha%20seat%20in%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99ll%20sit%20with%20national%20general%20secretary%20Abhishek%20Banerjee%20in%20a%20few%20days%20and%20decide%20on%20the%20number%20of%20seats%20we%20are%20going%20to%20contest%20in%20Assam%2C%E2%80%9D%20Dev%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EMamata%20Thakur%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EMamata%20Thakur%E2%80%99s%20nomination%20assumes%20significance%2C%20coming%2C%20coincidentally%20or%20not%2C%20exactly%20a%20day%20after%20Union%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20said%20that%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20(CAA)%20would%20be%20implemented%20across%20the%20country%20before%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20election.%20Notably%2C%20the%20current%20extension%20on%20framing%20Rules%20for%20the%20CAA%20ends%20on%20March%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fheres-why-the-bjp-brings-up-the-caa-but-stops-short-of-implementing-it-in-bengal%5C%22%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20Why%20the%20BJP%20Brings%20up%20the%20CAA%20%E2%80%93%20But%20Stops%20Short%20of%20Implementing%20it%20%E2%80%93%20in%20Bengal%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThakur%20heads%20one%20section%20of%20Matua%20Mahasangha%2C%20the%20most%20influential%20religious%20body%20of%20the%20Matua-Namasudra%20community%20that%20has%20emerged%20as%20the%20strongest%20votaries%20of%20the%20CAA%2C%20which%20grants%20citizenship%20to%20non-Muslims%20who%20have%20migrated%20from%20Muslim-majority%20neighbouring%20countries.%20The%20Matua-Namasudra%20community%20members%20have%20migrated%20from%20Bangladesh%20over%20the%20past%20several%20decades%2C%20many%20of%20them%20in%20the%20face%20of%20persecution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20TMC%20has%20vowed%20to%20prevent%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20CAA%20and%20Thakur%20has%20the%20herculean%20task%20of%20convicting%20the%20Matua-Namashudra%20community%20that%20the%20CAA%20would%20not%20be%20beneficial%20for%20them.%20The%20community%20plays%20the%20determining%20factor%20in%20at%20least%20two%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%2C%20Bongaon%20and%20Ranaghat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThakur%20was%20earlier%20a%20Lok%20Sabha%20MP%20from%20Bongaon%20but%20lost%20the%202019%20election%20to%20her%20nephew%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Shantanu%20Thakur%2C%20who%20heads%20the%20other%20faction%20of%20the%20Matua%20Mahasangha%20and%20is%20currently%20the%20junior%20shipping%20minister.%20Santanu%20Thakur%20had%20promised%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20CAA%20before%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EVeterans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20other%20TMC%20Rajya%20Sabha%20members%20are%20party%20veterans%20Subrata%20Bakshi%2C%20Derek%20O%E2%80%99Brien%2C%20and%20Sukhendu%20Sekhar%20Roy%2C%20north%20Bengal%E2%80%99s%20tribal%20leader%20Prakash%20Chik%20Baraik%20and%20social%20activist%20Samirul%20Islam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Rajya%20Sabha%20choice%2C%20Bhattacharya%2C%20has%20been%20a%20prominent%20face%20of%20the%20party%20since%20the%201990s.%20In%202014%2C%20he%20became%20the%20first%20BJP%20MLA%20in%20the%20state%20winning%20on%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20own%20strength.%20However%2C%20he%20lost%20in%20the%202016%20assembly%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CSending%20him%20to%20Rajya%20Sabha%20is%20a%20message%20to%20all%20veterans%20to%20have%20patience%20and%20faith%20on%20Modi-Shah%E2%80%99s%20leadership.%20Those%20who%20remain%20dedicated%20and%20disciplined%20will%20be%20rewarded%20on%20time.%20Bhattacharya%20remained%20quite%20cornered%20for%20much%20of%20the%20past%20few%20years%20but%20he%20never%20breached%20party%20discipline%20or%20became%20aloof%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20BJP%20state%20unit%20leader%20who%20did%20not%20want%20to%20be%20named.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EBJP%20currently%20has%20one%20Rajya%20Sabha%20member%20from%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Ananta%20Rai%2C%20who%20represents%20the%20Rajbanshi%20community%20of%20Cooch%20Behar%20and%20neighbouring%20districts%20in%20northern%20West%20Bengal%20but%20currently%20lives%20in%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707726654000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F12124835%2FUntitled-design-9-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftmc-rajya-sabha-sagarika-ghose-mamata-sushmita-dev%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22While%20the%20BJP%20named%20a%20Bengal%20unit%20veteran%20in%20an%20apparent%20move%20to%20assure%20old-timers%2C%20the%20choices%20made%20by%20Mamata%20Banerjee's%20party%20were%20interesting.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftmc-rajya-sabha-sagarika-ghose-mamata-sushmita-dev%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Family%20Animation%20%E2%80%98Ploey%202%20%E2%80%93%20The%20Legend%20of%20the%20Winds%E2%80%99%20to%20Launch%20into%20International%20Markets%20With%20The%20Playmaker%20(EXCLUSIVE)%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707726600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2FPLOEY-2.jpg%3Fw%3D1000%26h%3D563%26crop%3D1%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1235906705%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Playmaker%20has%20signed%20with%20GunHil%20to%20handle%20the%20world%20sales%20for%20%E2%80%9CPloey%202%20%E2%80%93%20The%20Legend%20of%20the%20Winds%2C%E2%80%9D%20which%20is%20described%20as%20%E2%80%9Can%20endearing%20and%20funny%20road%20movie%20for%20the%20whole%20family%20about%20pursuing%20your%20own%20ideals%20to%20serve%20the%20greater%20good.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Playmaker%20will%20present%20the%20film%20at%20the%20European%20Film%20Market%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Leo%20Barraclough%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fglobal%2Fploey-2-the-legend-of-the-winds-the-playmaker-1235906705%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fglobal%2Fploey-2-the-legend-of-the-winds-the-playmaker-1235906705%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fglobal%2Fploey-2-the-legend-of-the-winds-the-playmaker-1235906705%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Opinion%3A%20Sub-Grouping%20SCs%20%7C%20Prioritise-Not%20'Prefer'-Treating%20More%20Injured%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EConsider%20a%20hypothetical%20situation.%20You%20come%20across%20two%20injured%20and%20parched%20people.%20One%20is%20more%20severely%20injured%20than%20the%20other.%20You%20have%20a%20small%20bottle%20of%20water%20that%20will%20only%20suffice%20for%20one.%20Who%20will%20you%20give%20this%20water%20to%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20physical%20injuries%20such%20as%20bruises%2C%20lacerations%20and%20burns%2C%20injuries%20caused%20by%20discrimination%20may%20not%20be%20visible%20to%20the%20naked%20eye.%20It%20is%20hard%20to%20figure%20out%20who%20is%20injured%2C%20and%20in%20what%20ways.%20Among%20other%20things%2C%20empirical%20exercises%20such%20as%20censuses%20are%20helpful%20in%20viewing%20the%20aggregate%20effects%20of%20discrimination.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcaste-wise-population-census-not-enumerated-since-independence-minister-3622924%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOn%2520being%2520asked%2520the%2520details%2Cpublished%2520from%2520a%2520syndicated%2520feed.)%5C%22%3Ecensus%20of%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%20remains%20suspended%2C%20and%20the%20need%20for%20a%20caste%20census%20is%20selectively%20realised%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fbihar-caste-based-survey-ndtv-explains-4443519%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20state%20of%20Bihar%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Yet%2C%20statistical%20information%20is%20not%20the%20sole%20basis%20for%20state%20action.%20The%20executive%2C%20the%20legislature%20and%20the%20judiciary%20are%20frequently%20called%20upon%20to%20make%20decisions%20on%20matters%20of%20reservation%20and%20other%20forms%20of%20affirmative%20action.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EReservations%20Are%20Not%20'Exceptions'%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJudges%20have%20long%20delved%20into%20the%20doctrinal%20justifications%20for%20caste-based%20reservations%20since%20early%20days%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20decision%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EState%20of%20Madras%20v.%20Champakam%20Dorairajan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1951).%20These%20justifications%20have%20invoked%20constitutional%20ideas%20of%20a%20welfare%20state%2C%20equality%2C%20non-discrimination%2C%20equal%20opportunity%2C%20and%20adequate%20representation.%20Non-discrimination%20has%20been%20often%20invoked%20in%20opposition%20to%20reservations.%20In%20a%20paradox%20of%20sorts%2C%20this%20opposition%20views%20all%20caste-based%20reservations%20as%20fundamentally%20discriminatory.%20At%20the%20very%20best%2C%20begrudgingly%20or%20graciously%2C%20as%20a%20charitable%20concession%20perhaps%2C%20this%20opposition%20accepts%20reservations%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Bexception%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20principle%20of%20equality.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20it%20has%20taken%20an%20exceptionally%20large%20bench%20of%20nine%20Supreme%20Court%20judges%20in%3Cem%3E%20Indra%20Sawhney%20%26amp%3B%20Others%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20(1992)%2C%20to%20clarify%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ftopic%2Freservations%5C%22%3Ereservations%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20not%20exceptions%20but%20provisions%20of%20equality.%20The%20doctrinal%20understanding%20of%20affirmative%20action%20in%20the%20US%20has%20taken%20similarly%20dialectical%20positions.%20The%20more%20avid%20supporters%20of%20affirmative%20action%20characterise%20it%20as%20a%20remedy%20against%20discrimination%3B%20other%20supporters%20characterise%20it%20as%20an%20exception%20to%20the%20anti-discrimination%20doctrine%2C%20while%20the%20opposition%20characterise%20affirmative%20action%20as%20an%20unjustifiable%20%26quot%3Bpreferential%20treatment%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20impugned%20legislation%20currently%20pending%20adjudication%20appears%20to%20have%20lapsed%20into%20the%20framework%20of%20preference.%20Section%204(5)%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fstates-cant-be-selective-in-granting-quota-to-backward-classes-supreme-court-5020583%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520Chinnaiah%2520judgment%2520had%2520held%2CArticle%2520341%2520of%2520the%2520Constitution.%5C%22%3EPunjab%20Scheduled%20Castes%20and%20Backward%20Classes%3C%2Fa%3E%20(Reservation%20in%20Services)%20Act%2C%202006%20provides%20%26quot%3Ba%20first%20preference%26quot%3B%20to%20Balmikis%20and%20Mazhabi%20Sikhs%20in%2050%25%20of%20the%20quota%20reserved%20for%20Scheduled%20Castes%20(SC).%20A%20five-judge%20constitution%20bench%20in%20%3Cem%3EE.V.%20Chinnaiah%20v%20State%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2004)%20had%20disallowed%20such%20subclassification%20because%20it%20was%20considered%20manipulation%20of%20the%20originally%20notified%20list%20of%20the%20SC.%20Now%2C%20the%20fate%20of%20the%20impugned%20provision%20hangs%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20a%20larger%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fall-scs-sts-may-not-be-homogenous-supreme-court-on-sub-classification-5013359%5C%22%3Eseven-judge%20constitutional%20bench%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EThe%20'Creamy%20Layer'%20Debate%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20word%20'preference'%20has%20invoked%20corresponding%20ideas%20of%20preferential%20treatment%20that%20are%20inimical%20to%20the%20doctrinal%20foundations%20of%20reservations.%20It%20invokes%20the%20same%20dialectical%20positions%20previously%20raised%20between%20the%20reserved%20categories%20of%20the%20SC%20and%20the%20unreserved%20General%20categories.%20Only%20now%20must%20the%20so-called%20preferential%20treatment%20be%20justified%20within%20the%20SC%20categories%2C%20setting%20intense%20intra-group%20rivalries%20among%20the%20SCs.%20Troubling%20questions%20arise%20over%20who%20is%20more%20discriminated%20against%2C%20more%20dehumanised%2C%20subordinated%2C%20marginalised%2C%20disadvantaged%2C%20oppressed%2C%20silenced%2C%20erased%2C%20and%20victimised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20opens%20the%20Pandora's%20box%20of%20%26quot%3Bcreamy%20layer%26quot%3B%2C%20a%20juridical%20invention%20of%20Indra%20Sawhney%20(1992)%20that%20sought%20to%20distinguish%20a%20relatively%20better-off%20segment%20among%20the%20Backward%20Classes%20(BC)%20from%20the%20actual%20backward%20classes-leading%20to%20wide%20intra-group%20resentment%20and%20contestations.%20Similarly%20divisive%20sentiments%20are%20now%20being%20raised%20among%20anti-caste%20Dalit%20groups.%20Some%20SC%20groups%20invoke%20their%20experiences%20of%20caste-based%20%26quot%3Buntouchability%26quot%3B%20as%20a%20distinguishing%20factor%20from%20the%20BC%2C%20thereby%20rendering%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20creamy%20layer%20inapplicable%20to%20the%20SC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Justice%20Gavai%20has%20pointed%20to%20internal%20hierarchies%20and%20historical%20practices%20of%20%26quot%3Buntouchability%26quot%3B%20among%20the%20SC%20groups.%20He%20reportedly%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWere%20they%20(scavengers)%20not%20untouchables%20amongst%20the%20untouchables%3F%26quot%3B%20This%20slippery%20slope%20will%20raise%20more%20questions%20about%20the%20caste-specificity%20in%20the%20Scheduled%20Castes%20and%20the%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(Prevention%20of%20Atrocities)%20Act%2C%201989%2C%20such%20that%20the%20SC%20persons%20cannot%20be%20perpetrators%20of%20offences%20(under%20Section%203%20thereof)%20against%20other%20SC%20persons.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EOn%20Substantive%20Equality%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20conundrum%20is%2C%20inadvertently%20and%20partly%2C%20an%20offshoot%20of%20the%20preferential%20treatment%20discourse.%20In%20the%20first%20instance%2C%20it%20could%20have%20been%20avoided%20by%20substituting%20the%20word%20'preference'%20with%20priority%20in%20the%20Punjab%20Act.%20It%20would%20only%20be%20a%20minor%20discursive%20strategy%2C%20a%20sidestepping%20of%20sorts.%20It%20would%20not%20make%20a%20substantial%20difference.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20has%20obliquely%20hinted%2C%20the%20existing%20jurisprudence%20on%20substantive%20equality%20in%20India%20is%20robust%20enough%20to%20uphold%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20sub-classification%20of%20SC%20groups.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20conclusion%2C%20to%20answer%20the%20hypothetical%20question%20at%20the%20start%20of%20this%20opinion%2C%20if%20I%20were%20a%20functionary%20of%20the%20state%2C%20I%20would%20give%20respite%20to%20the%20one%20who%20is%20more%20severely%20injured.%20I%20would%20do%20this%20as%20a%20reasoned%20prioritising%20(of%20scarce%20resources)%2C%20not%20as%20a%20whimsical%20preference%20of%20one%20subordinate%20group%20over%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3E(Prof.%20Dr.%20Sumit%20Baudh%20(they%2F%20he)%20teaches%20constitutional%20law.%20Views%20in%20this%20opinion%20are%20informed%20by%20their%20comparative%20understanding%20of%20Critical%20Race%20Theory.%20He%20can%20be%20reached%20on%20X%20%40BaudhSumit)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707726540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2Fe8bgk2vo_supreme-court-getty_625x300_31_October_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findia-supreme-court-sub-classifying-scs-scheduled-castes-lets-prioritise-not-prefer-treating-the-more-injured-first-5041896%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22More%20than%20just%20a%20whimsical%20preferential%20treatment%20of%20one%20group%20over%20the%20other%2C%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20debate%20is%20the%20question%20of%20which%20are%20the%20more%20injured%20groups%20that%20the%20state%20needs%20to%20prioritise%20for%20affirmative%20action.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findia-supreme-court-sub-classifying-scs-scheduled-castes-lets-prioritise-not-prefer-treating-the-more-injured-first-5041896%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findia-supreme-court-sub-classifying-scs-scheduled-castes-lets-prioritise-not-prefer-treating-the-more-injured-first-5041896%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findia-supreme-court-sub-classifying-scs-scheduled-castes-lets-prioritise-not-prefer-treating-the-more-injured-first-5041896%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Israel%20rescues%20two%20hostages%20in%20Rafah%20amid%20deadly%20strikes%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1707726346000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F53FE%2Fproduction%2F_132620512_hostagescomposite-reuters.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-68271340%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20military%20says%20the%20pair%20are%20in%20%26quot%3Bgood%20medical%20condition%26quot%3B%3B%20meanwhile%20deadly%20attacks%20have%20been%20reported%20in%20Gaza.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1076%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-68271340%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-68271340.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-68271340.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20%E2%80%98Hindu%20Atheist%E2%80%99%20Who%20Cracked%20the%20Glass%20Ceiling%20in%20UK%20Politics%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F12131838%2F1200px-Official_portrait_of_Baroness_Flather_crop_2_2019.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20prime%20ministers%20of%20Britain%20and%20of%20Ireland%20both%20visited%20Belfast%20in%20British-ruled%20Northern%20Ireland%20the%20other%20day.%20One%20of%20them%2C%20Rishi%20Sunak%2C%20is%20of%20Punjabi%20descent%3B%20the%20other%2C%20Leo%20Varadkar%2C%20has%20family%20roots%20in%20Mumbai%20where%20he%20spent%20part%20of%20his%20childhood.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20occasion%20was%20the%20restoration%20of%20devolved%20government%20in%20Northern%20Ireland%20after%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20of%20political%20stalemate.%20A%20big%20event%20%E2%80%93%20but%20I%20want%20to%20dwell%20on%20the%20subject%20that%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20touched%20on%20in%20the%20news%20coverage.%20No%20one%20commented%20on%20these%20two%20prime%20ministers%20both%20being%20of%20Indian%20heritage.%20It%20is%2C%20quite%20literally%2C%20unremarkable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20children%20and%20grandchildren%20of%20immigrants%20are%20now%20so%20prominent%20in%20British%20(and%20Irish)%20public%20life%2C%20it%20is%20easy%20to%20forget%20just%20how%20unrelentingly%20white%20the%20political%20landscape%20was%20just%20a%20generation%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBack%20in%20the%20late%201980s%2C%20I%20landed%20what%20I%20regarded%20then%20as%20my%20dream%20job.%20I%20became%20a%20BBC%20political%20correspondent.%20In%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%2C%20there%20were%20just%20four%20Black%20and%20Asian%20Members%20of%20Parliament.%20And%20all%20four%20were%20still%20then%20newcomers%20to%20Westminster.%20There%20had%20been%20Indian%20MPs%20in%20earlier%20years%20%E2%80%93%20men%20such%20as%20Dadabhai%20Naoroji%20and%20Shapurji%20Saklatvala%20%E2%80%93%20but%20for%20decades%20until%20the%201987%20election%2C%20the%20Commons%20had%20been%20entirely%20white.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20was%20still%20reporting%20on%20Westminster%20when%20Shreela%20Flather%20%E2%80%93%20who%20died%20last%20week%20just%20short%20of%20her%2090th%20birthday%20%E2%80%93%20was%20nominated%20to%20the%20unelected%20upper%20chamber%20of%20Parliament%2C%20the%20House%20of%20Lords.%20That%20was%20in%201990.%20She%20was%20the%20first%20Asian%20woman%20to%20take%20a%20seat%20in%20the%20Lords.%20She%20had%20earlier%20been%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20first%20Asian%20woman%20magistrate%20and%20the%20first%20Asian%20woman%20to%20be%20a%20local%20mayor.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20her%20elevation%20to%20the%20Lords%2C%20the%20number%20of%20ethnic%20minority%20peers%20doubled.%20The%20other%20minority%20peer%20back%20then%20was%20Lord%20Pitt%2C%20a%20doctor%20and%20Labour%20politician%20who%20was%20born%20in%20Grenada%20in%20the%20Caribbean.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBaroness%20Flather%2C%20a%20Conservative%2C%20was%20at%20that%20time%20her%20party%E2%80%99s%20only%20non-white%20parliamentarian%20in%20either%20the%20Commons%20or%20the%20Lords.%20She%20made%20herself%20noticed%2C%20not%20least%20by%20wearing%20a%20sari%20in%20the%20ever-so-formal%20setting%20of%20the%20House%20of%20Lords%20chamber.%20She%20was%20not%20a%20political%20heavyweight%3B%20she%20was%20never%20a%20government%20minister.%20But%20she%20was%20friendly%2C%20accessible%20%E2%80%93%20and%20determined%20to%20make%20her%20mark.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20she%20succeeded.%20Not%20many%20parliamentarians%20can%20point%20to%20something%20that%20is%20their%20particular%20achievement.%20But%20her%20energetic%20advocacy%20of%20and%20fund-raising%20for%20a%20memorial%20to%20the%20five-million%20soldiers%2C%20sailors%20and%20airmen%20from%20the%20Indian%20subcontinent%2C%20Africa%20and%20the%20Caribbean%20who%20served%20in%20two%20world%20wars%20was%20crowned%20with%20success.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Memorial%20Gates%20close%20to%20Buckingham%20Palace%20were%20inaugurated%20by%20Queen%20Elizabeth%20in%202002.%20A%20commemorative%20event%20is%20held%20there%20every%20March%20on%20Commonwealth%20Day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20brought%20up%20a%20Hindu%2C%20Shreela%20Flather%20regarded%20herself%20as%20an%20atheist%20(or%20sometimes%20as%20a%20Hindu%20atheist%2C%20which%20of%20course%20is%20not%20quite%20such%20a%20contradiction%20as%20it%20would%20be%20for%20other%20global%20religions).%20She%20supported%20groups%20such%20as%20the%20National%20Secular%20Society%20and%20Humanists%20UK%20which%20campaign%20against%20the%20influence%20of%20organised%20religion%20in%20public%20life.%20She%20also%20was%20for%20many%20years%20the%20chair%20of%20Marie%20Stopes%20International%2C%20which%20provides%20sexual%20and%20reproductive%20health%20information.%20This%20is%20not%20the%20normal%20range%20of%20causes%20for%20a%20Conservative%20peer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20also%20had%20a%20compelling%20back%20story.%20Baroness%20Flather%20was%20born%20Shreela%20Rai%20into%20a%20prosperous%20Hindu%20family%20in%20Lahore.%20Sir%20Ganga%20Ram%2C%20the%20celebrated%20Punjabi%20civil%20engineer%20and%20philanthropist%2C%20was%20her%20great-grandfather.%20At%20Partition%2C%20the%20family%20fled%20to%20Delhi.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20Shreela%E2%80%99s%20father%20was%20appointed%20India%E2%80%99s%20ambassador%20to%20Brazil.%20She%20came%20to%20London%20to%20study%20law%20in%201952.%20Her%20first%20husband%20had%20been%20a%20captain%20in%20the%20British%20army.%20That%20marriage%20ended%20in%20divorce.%20Her%20second%20husband%2C%20a%20British%20barrister%2C%20died%20seven%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShreela%20Flather%20took%20up%20issues%20of%20importance%20to%20British%20Asians%20%E2%80%93%20for%20example%2C%20seeking%20to%20change%20rules%20on%20school%20uniform%20which%20discriminated%20against%20Asian%20pupils.%20She%20was%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Race%20Relations%20Board%20and%20later%20the%20Commission%20for%20Racial%20Equality.%20She%20described%20the%20police%20as%20%E2%80%98institutionally%20racist%E2%80%99%20before%20the%20full%20weight%20of%20police%20prejudice%20against%20people%20of%20colour%20was%20widely%20understood.%20And%20she%20had%20to%20face%20racism%20within%20her%20own%20party.%20It%E2%80%99s%20said%20that%20when%20she%20first%20spoke%20at%20a%20Conservative%20Party%20conference%2C%20she%20was%20spat%20at.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20Flather%E2%80%99s%20views%2C%20however%2C%20were%20themselves%20denounced%20as%20racist.%20She%20called%20for%20DNA%20tests%20to%20combat%20the%20practice%20among%20some%20Muslim%20communities%20of%20first%20cousins%20marrying.%20She%20proposed%20a%20ban%20on%20halal%20meat.%20And%20she%20commented%20that%20some%20immigrant%20groups%2C%20particularly%20those%20from%20Pakistan%20and%20Bangladesh%2C%20deliberately%20had%20lots%20of%20children%20so%20they%20could%20claim%20more%20in%20welfare%20benefits.%20Indian%20families%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%20%E2%80%93%20she%20said%20%E2%80%93%20%C2%A0%E2%80%98are%20like%20the%20Jews%20of%20old.%20They%20want%20their%20children%20to%20be%20educated.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20she%20had%20a%20reputation%20for%20%E2%80%98saying%20the%20unsayable%E2%80%99%2C%20she%20conceded%20that%20she%20had%20on%20occasions%20%E2%80%98gone%20too%20far%E2%80%99.%20And%20she%20certainly%20caused%20offence%20to%20British%20Muslims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBaroness%20Flather%20left%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20in%202008%2C%20continuing%20to%20sit%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Lords%20without%20a%20party%20affiliation.%20She%20was%20unquestionably%20a%20pioneer%2C%20with%20the%20strength%20of%20character%20to%20succeed%20in%20areas%20which%20were%20not%20then%20welcoming%20to%20Asians%2C%20and%20certainly%20not%20to%20Asian%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20managed%20to%20crack%20the%20glass%20ceiling%20that%20hitherto%20had%20constrained%20the%20rise%20in%20politics%20of%20British%20Asians%2C%20however%20talented.%20There%20are%20now%2066%20MPs%20and%2055%20members%20of%20the%20House%20of%20Lords%20who%20are%20from%20an%20ethnic%20minority.%20Rishi%20Sunak%20and%20others%20have%20smashed%20that%20glass%20ceiling%20into%20tiny%20pieces.%20But%20in%20doing%20so%20they%20were%20standing%20on%20the%20shoulders%2C%20metaphorically%20at%20least%2C%20of%20the%20diminutive%20Shreela%20Flather.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Ffrino%5C%22%3EAndrew%20Whitehead%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20an%20honorary%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Nottingham%20in%20the%20UK%20and%20a%20former%20BBC%20India%20correspondent.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3ELondon%20Calling%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0How%20does%20India%20look%20from%20afar%3F%20Looming%20world%20power%20or%20dysfunctional%20democracy%3F%20And%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20in%20Britain%2C%20and%20the%20West%2C%20that%20India%20needs%20t